CatDescriptText: Cutline of article published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 10, 1953, pg. 12 reads: "Pittsburgh's second Debutante Cotillion was dramatized beautifully last Monday night in Syria Mosque with the flavor-of-winter, overlain with beauty and the delicate charm that perfumes the air when youth reigns supreme. Once again sorors of Alpha Kappa Alpha may take a curtsey for their artistic success and their contribution to the culture of our community..."
TitMainTitle: Debutantes and escorts, including "King" Roland Dent and "Queen" Bernistine McClaney wearing crowns, walking in couples in Syria Mosque for the 1953 Alpha Kappa Alpha cotillion
